SIMPLE: dextro
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dextro-
<hw>Dex"tro-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A prefix, from L.
<ets>dexter</ets>, meaning, pertaining to, or toward, the
<sig>right</sig></def>; <fld>(Chem. & Opt.)</fld> <def>having the
property of turning the plane of polarized light to the
<sig>right</sig>; <as>as, <ex>dextro</ex>tartaric acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dextrogerous</ent>⟦br⟧
